35:46.240 --> 35:47.720
- Are you married?
- No.

35:47.960 --> 35:48.960
Makes sense.

35:49.120 --> 35:50.600
What's that suppose to mean?

35:51.040 --> 35:52.240
Your shoes are polished.

35:52.360 --> 35:55.200
Your shirt came from a laundry,
but you have a spot on your tie.

35:55.400 --> 35:57.360
You have people to look
after your hygiene

35:57.560 --> 35:58.920
but nobody to look at you.

35:59.040 --> 36:00.840
Your wife would have seen the spot.

36:01.840 --> 36:05.400
Agent Austiger,
how about I buy you a beer?

36:06.080 --> 36:08.240
- Ooh. A beer sounds good.
- We make our own.

36:08.440 --> 36:09.600
Now.

36:10.600 --> 36:13.600
Yeah. Why don't you guys
come back in like an hour.

36:20.640 --> 36:22.120
So guys...

36:25.200 --> 36:26.200
What are you doing?

36:26.400 --> 36:28.560
Oh, shit. Hang on.
Hold that thought.

36:28.760 --> 36:29.920
I've got to...

36:30.600 --> 36:33.000
I've been waiting for...
Yeah, it's my lab, I've got to take this.

36:33.240 --> 36:34.080
What?

36:34.160 --> 36:36.360
<i>- Mexico City is in trouble, David.
- What?</i>

36:36.720 --> 36:38.920
General Carvajale called
extremely apologetic.

36:39.000 --> 36:40.440
A lot of good that does us now.

36:40.480 --> 36:42.120
It seems in the mountains,
outside the city,

36:42.200 --> 36:44.240
slightly acidic rain
is beginning to fall.

36:44.280 --> 36:46.800
If I'm right,
concentrated sulfuric acid

36:47.040 --> 36:48.920
- will hit before daylight.
- You are right, Bob.

36:49.120 --> 36:51.040
You've been right every
step of the way.

36:51.520 --> 36:54.600
David, I've tried to neutralize
the cloud with bicarbonate of soda.

36:54.640 --> 36:56.400
- The acid is too concentrated?
- Yes.

36:56.520 --> 36:58.920
And I don't have enough time
to test every other base.

36:59.040 --> 37:00.800
Okay, we got one shot at this.
Hang on a second.

37:00.880 --> 37:03.160
What's the best way to
neutralize sulfuric acid ?

37:03.480 --> 37:05.320
A strong alkaline solution.

37:05.400 --> 37:08.920
- But if the acid's too strong, the combination could explode.
- Up in the atmosphere.

37:10.000 --> 37:12.280
- Ammonia.
- Oh geez! Yeah.

37:12.480 --> 37:13.560
Bob, ammonia.

37:13.680 --> 37:16.600
I mean, I know it's volatile. I know
it's toxic but it's a hell of an alkali.

37:16.720 --> 37:17.760
- May I?
- That's true.

37:17.960 --> 37:19.360
Bob, I'm going to put
you on speaker.

37:20.720 --> 37:23.600
What's the sulfuric acid content
in the atmosphere right now?

37:23.880 --> 37:26.240
According to the NOAA, 14 million tons.

37:26.400 --> 37:28.200
- 14 million tons.
- That's a lot.

37:28.760 --> 37:30.880
Okay. How much ammonia
do we have to add?

37:31.000 --> 37:32.600
- To neutralize it?
- Yeah.

37:32.720 --> 37:34.560
What's the molecular
weight of sulfuric acid ?

37:34.840 --> 37:37.600
- H2SO4. Sulphur is 35.
- 4 Oxygens is 64.

37:37.680 --> 37:38.840
And 2 Hydrogens... 101.

37:40.120 --> 37:41.880
Okay. Molecular weight of ammonia?

37:41.960 --> 37:43.240
17.

37:47.160 --> 37:50.640
- 2.356 Million tons.
- That's a lot of ammonia.

37:52.040 --> 37:54.880
Worst case scenario, Bob,
if we can't get it in the clouds?

37:55.040 --> 37:58.040
Well, if we don't get enough in there
the acid rain comes down...

37:58.520 --> 38:01.280
- in a monsoon.
- Jesus.

38:02.000 --> 38:03.760
Anybody got any better ideas?

38:05.440 --> 38:08.440
- A catalyst to reduce the acid?
- A platinum catalyst transformation...

38:08.680 --> 38:10.960
- But that would take ten years.
- And a lot of money...

38:11.160 --> 38:12.880
Go with the ammonia, Bob.

38:13.120 --> 38:14.920
- Good work.
- Okay. Bye.

38:16.600 --> 38:19.080
- What was that?
- There's this cloud hanging

38:19.240 --> 38:22.120
over Mexico City chock full of SO2,
and one of my guys thinks

38:22.320 --> 38:25.880
it's about to dump concentrated
sulfuric acid down on everything.

38:26.120 --> 38:27.720
He's been tracking it for a week.

38:27.880 --> 38:30.280
I got taken off the case
because Homeland Security thinks

38:30.320 --> 38:32.720
that two brilliant scientists
are trying to kill the President

38:32.800 --> 38:34.760
- of the United States.
- That's not true.

38:34.880 --> 38:37.040
We're sorry for taking
you away from your clouds.

38:37.200 --> 38:40.240
Don't worry about it. We're taking
a chance, but we think we got it.

38:40.320 --> 38:42.520
It's sad. How we destroy our planet.

38:43.400 --> 38:45.960
Anyway, going back to what you
were saying about retrotransposition.

38:46.640 --> 38:48.840
All these yeast samples in your lab.

38:48.960 --> 38:53.080
Are you proposing to use yeast
as a model for retrovirus life cycle?

38:55.120 --> 38:57.840
Come on guys. Am I going to have
to test everything in your lab?

38:57.960 --> 39:00.720
because that's what they want me to do and
that's what these morons are going to make me do,

39:00.920 --> 39:03.520
test every goddamn thing
right down to your pipettes.

39:03.680 --> 39:06.920
- You don't have to do that.
- Then tell me what you're trying to do?

39:08.000 --> 39:11.720
Are you trying to make a drug
to inhibit retrotransposition?

39:13.920 --> 39:16.280
I'm on your side, guys.

39:21.160 --> 39:23.160
Well. We're hoping the yeast

39:23.320 --> 39:26.280
will give us different
ways to combat HIV.

39:28.080 --> 39:29.640
So you're...

39:30.320 --> 39:33.080
You're testing for HIV
inhibitors in a yeast model?

39:33.360 --> 39:35.240
Not testing. Not exactly.

39:35.360 --> 39:38.200
- The yeast is more of a vector.
- A delivery system.

39:38.360 --> 39:42.040
You see, the world
doesn't need more HIV drugs.

39:42.200 --> 39:44.520
What the world needs
is a way to prevent people

39:44.600 --> 39:47.000
- from getting sick in the first place.
- A vaccine.

39:47.400 --> 39:51.040
Yes. But, look at Hepatitis vaccines.
They exist.

39:51.440 --> 39:54.960
They're available, but do the poor
and disenfranchised get them?

39:55.680 --> 39:58.280
- We're thinking of something a little different.
- Vincent.

39:59.360 --> 40:00.360
It's alright.

40:00.480 --> 40:03.040
- Please.
- No, no. Vincent. Vincent, keep going.

40:03.320 --> 40:06.000
So, you're making a vaccine in yeast.
How is that going to help?

40:06.120 --> 40:09.400
There's a lot of vaccines made in yeast and
that doesn't make them more available to the poor.

40:09.520 --> 40:11.440
I'm not talking about a vaccine in yeast.

40:11.600 --> 40:14.720
- I'm talking about yeast.
- Vincent, please!

40:19.480 --> 40:21.920
I'm just pondering, perhaps

40:22.160 --> 40:25.880
the method of delivery
for hepatitis vaccines is inefficient.

40:26.760 --> 40:29.240
What? Like what,
there's not enough needles?

40:35.200 --> 40:37.000
Oh! No fucking way.

40:38.440 --> 40:41.520
You guys are trying to find
a way to put a vaccine in bread?

40:42.360 --> 40:44.360
That is fucking brilliant!

40:45.400 --> 40:48.520
Wai-wai-wait.
What about thermostability?

40:48.640 --> 40:50.400
How is the vaccine going
to survive the baking?

40:52.080 --> 40:55.720
Come on, guys, tell me, I'm not
gonna fucking scoop you! Tell me!

40:57.960 --> 41:00.000
I figured that part out long ago.

41:00.240 --> 41:03.160
With everything I saw in their lab,
their idea makes perfect sense.

41:03.320 --> 41:06.560
Actually, it makes perfect brilliant sense.
I can see why they weren't keen to share.

41:06.640 --> 41:09.320
I know plenty of scientists
who would scoop them in a second.

41:10.240 --> 41:11.920
Are you satisfied with this?

41:12.160 --> 41:14.760
It's not a question
of my own satisfaction.

41:19.840 --> 41:21.400
They missed it, Vincent.

41:21.560 --> 41:23.600
We knew they would, Stefan.

41:35.440 --> 41:36.840
Yeah, we just landed.

41:37.640 --> 41:40.640
No, she took a cab home.
What's going on?

41:43.880 --> 41:46.920
Well, it doesn't sound like there's
anything I can do about it tonight so...

41:47.600 --> 41:50.720
Yeah, well I'll be home
if anything changes, okay Bob?

41:51.680 --> 41:52.680
Oh. And Bob...

41:52.800 --> 41:55.000
if you can,
try to get some sleep.

41:56.560 --> 41:58.200
I said if you can, Bob.

42:57.320 --> 42:59.120
Bob, have you got the results?

42:59.360 --> 43:01.680
- It's not going to work, Carlos?
- Why?

43:01.800 --> 43:04.480
The ammonia, we can't get enough of it.
It'll rain acid.

43:04.680 --> 43:06.200
It's not going to work.

43:13.000 --> 43:15.000
We only have a few hours left.

43:20.840 --> 43:22.840
Forget it, we're not going
to get enough ammonia.

43:22.920 --> 43:26.000
No, even if we tapped into US supplies
and got them here in time.

43:26.200 --> 43:29.160
350,000 metric tonnes would only
bring the pH of the cloud up to 2.5.

43:29.320 --> 43:30.840
So, we need something else.

43:33.000 --> 43:36.720
This chick called last night,
said, Harlan died.

43:37.280 --> 43:39.480
I think Harlan left us something.

43:39.800 --> 43:42.720
He said what he was working on
could be a potential moneymaker.

43:42.840 --> 43:44.600
He said even millions.

43:45.000 --> 43:48.160
Actually I think these genes
have to do with sexual reproduction.

43:48.400 --> 43:50.200
Multiple orgasms, I'd pay for that.

43:50.400 --> 43:52.240
A fifty percent increase in suicides?

43:52.440 --> 43:55.520
And you don't think it's related
to the hurricane damage Katrina caused?

43:55.720 --> 43:57.000
Suicides don't spread.

43:57.200 --> 43:59.880
- Usually, there are different
suicide rates for males and females.

44:00.040 --> 44:02.200
- Different races.
- True, but in the counties

44:02.320 --> 44:05.160
in the 50% zone, the results are
the same across all demographics.

44:05.280 --> 44:06.200
Even kids.

44:06.320 --> 44:07.960
Two hundred bucks
missing from my wallet.

44:08.120 --> 44:09.320
- Owen?
- No, elves.

44:09.440 --> 44:11.160
I saw him about an hour ago
and he was flying.

44:11.400 --> 44:13.000
- On what?
- Meth.

44:15.160 --> 44:16.800
What did you do?
Rob a Starbucks?

44:18.480 --> 44:21.040
- I'm... I'm sick, man. I--
- What do you want, Owen?

44:21.640 --> 44:25.440
It's cold on the street, and I know...
I need to get better.

44:25.600 --> 44:27.480
I don't want you
to get hurt by Owen, okay?

44:27.560 --> 44:29.240
You can't trust him.

